ns0:trans-unit.ns0:source: 0 means the password is extremely easy to guess (within 10^3 guesses). Dictionary words like "password" or "mother" score 0.

ns0:trans-unit.ns0:source: 1 is still very easy to guess (guesses less than 10^6). An extra character on a dictionary word can score 1.
ns0:trans-unit.ns0:target: 1 хали жуда осон тахмин қилиш мумкин (10^6 дан кам тахмин). Луғат сўзига қўшимча белги 1 балл олиши мумкин.

ns0:trans-unit.ns0:source: 2 is pretty easy to guess (guesses less than 10^8). It provides some protection from unthrottled online attacks.

ns0:trans-unit.ns0:source: 3 is safely unguessable (guesses less than 10^10). It offers moderate protection from offline slow-hash scenario.

ns0:trans-unit.ns0:source: 4 is very unguessable (guesses greater than or equal to 10^10) and provides strong protection from offline slow-hash scenario.
